**Segments**

- By Design IP (Processor IP, Interface IP, Memory IP, Other IP)
- By IP Source (Licensing, Royalty)
- By IP Core (Hard IP, Soft IP)

The semiconductor IP market is segmented based on various criteria to provide a deeper understanding of the industry dynamics. The first segment, Design IP, includes Processor IP, Interface IP, Memory IP, and Other IP. These different categories cater to specific needs within the semiconductor industry, enabling companies to customize their products based on the required functionality and performance. The second segment, IP Source, encompasses Licensing and Royalty models. This differentiation is crucial as it influences how companies acquire and utilize semiconductor IP, impacting their cost structures and strategic partnerships. The third segment, IP Core, comprises Hard IP and Soft IP. The distinction between these core types affects the flexibility and ease of integration of semiconductor IP into existing systems, influencing product development timelines and overall efficiency.

